# ── Trust Tiers (→895) ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Trust is determined by GPG web of trust, not by platform accounts.
# Your tier is resolved at boot from cross-signatures in your keyring.
#
#   T0 — Dual-signed (human + kernel). Full governance. No restrictions.
#         Key is a T0 trust anchor OR cross-signed by root.
#   T1 — Key cross-signed by a T0 holder. Write access to src.
#         OS files protected (deny: write-kernel modify-governance).
#   T2 — GPG key present, NOT cross-signed. Read-only.
#         (deny: write-kernel modify-governance write-src).
#   T3 — No GPG key. Anonymous. Cannot boot. Public artifacts only.
#
# Escalation path: T3 → get a GPG key → T2 → get cross-signed by T0 → T1
# To get cross-signed: share your fingerprint with a T0 holder.
# They sign your key: gpg --sign-key YOUR_FINGERPRINT
# You import: gpg --import their-signed-key.asc
# Now your key carries a T0 signature. Boot again → T1.

