# ── Secrets ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Keys never enter LLM context. The kernel resolves secrets in order:
#
#   1. ostk secret store    — `ostk secret set KEY` stores in platform keychain
#                              (macOS Keychain / Linux secret-tool)
#   2. BYO secret manager   — set OSTK_SECRET_CMD to your tool (bw, op, pass)
#   3. Environment variable — fallback to $KEY in your shell env
#
# To add a key:    ostk secret set ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
# To check status: ostk secret list
#
# You only need the key(s) for your chosen provider:
#   - claude-*     → ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
#   - gemini-*     → GEMINI_API_KEY (or GOOGLE_API_KEY)
#   - mistral-*    → MISTRAL_API_KEY
#   - codestral-*  → MISTRAL_API_KEY
#   - openrouter/* → OPENROUTER_API_KEY
#   - openai-*     → OPENAI_API_KEY

SECRET <<KEYS
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
GEMINI_API_KEY
GOOGLE_API_KEY
MISTRAL_API_KEY
OPENROUTER_API_KEY
OPENAI_API_KEY
KEYS

# ── PIN Policy (→895) ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# PINs are capability boundaries. They define what agents CAN'T do.
# The OS enforces them invisibly at the write path.
#
# With v2.2.1, pins are automatic — your trust tier determines your
# default restrictions. No OSTK_PIN env var needed.
#
# Tier-default pins:
#
#   T0: no restrictions (full governance)
#   T1: deny write-kernel modify-governance
#   T2: deny write-kernel modify-governance write-src
#   T3: deny all writes (cannot boot)
#
# Explicit pins (via `ostk run --pin <name>`) can only ADD restrictions
# on top of your tier default. The tier is a floor, not an override.
# A T2 user cannot escape write-src denial via an explicit pin.
#
# Custom pins:
#   ostk pin issue my-agent --caps "read write execute"
#   # then edit .ostk/pins/my-agent/pin.caps
#
# Default deny tokens:
#
#   write-kernel         Agents cannot modify .ostk/ (the OS state)
#   modify-governance    Agents cannot modify HUMANFILE, ENTITYFILE,
#                        .primefile, GOVERNANCE.md, Agentfile, or
#                        anything in agents/
#   write-src            Agents cannot modify files under src/

